sentences: Henry George Farmer (17 January 1882 – 20 December 1965) was a British musicologist and Arabist.
His mother, Mary Ann Harling (1850-1907), was related to Afflecks and Allans of Scotland.

Farmer was born in Crinkill Barracks, near Birr, Offaly (Kings County), Ireland, where his father, also Henry George Farmer (1848-1900), was stationed with the Prince of Wales's Leinster Regiment of the British Army.
His nephew was John Farmer (1835-1901), also a music teacher, organist and composer.
An earlier Henry Farmer (1819-1891) had composed popular liturgy - Mass in B-flat and concertos.
